  "instructions": [
    "Heat olive oil in a large pot over medium heat.",
    "Dice potatoes, chop onion, mince garlic, and grate ginger.",
    "Add onion to the pot and sauté until translucent.",
    "Stir in garlic and ginger, cooking for 1 minute until fragrant.",
    "Add potato cubes and stir to coat with oil and spices.",
    "Pour in vegetable broth, add tomato paste, tandoori spice mix, salt, and pepper, stirring well.",
    "Bring the mixture to a gentle boil, then reduce heat, cover, and simmer for 15 minutes until potatoes are tender.",
    "Stir in coconut milk, bring to a low simmer, and cook for an additional 5 minutes until the sauce thickens.",
    "Taste and adjust seasoning if needed.",
    "Remove from heat, stir in chopped cilantro, and serve hot."
  ],
